<title>USA: Fluor wins $1 billion Indonesia project.</title>
<headline>Fluor wins $1 billion Indonesia project.</headline>
<dateline>IRVINE, Calif.</dateline>
<text>
<p>Fluor Daniel, a unit of Fluor Corp., said Tuesday it was awarded a contract valued at more than $1 billion for engineering and construction services on a huge Indonesian copper and gold mining project.</p>
<p>The Batu Hijau project is a large copper and gold deposit on the island of Sumbawa Batu Hijau, with an estimated 11.2 billion pounds of copper and 14.7 million ounces of gold.</p>
<p>Newmont Gold Co. and Japan's Sumitomo Corp. signed an agreement in July to jointly develop the project.</p>
<p>Under the terms of the agreement, Newmont holds a 45 percent stake in the project and Sumitomo, a 35 percent interest.</p>
<p>The remaining 20 percent is held by a local Indonesian company.</p>
